  "text": "We have also considered a basic XML encryption [CITATION_1] protocol. It is a very simple protocol between two principals A and B that share an encryption key k and a MAC key k . In order to encrypt a list a 1 , . . . , a M using the encryptthen-MAC scheme, one encrypts each component of the list, and computes a MAC of the list of ciphertexts:",
